## ApiSources-D1 Model-First Agent Configuration Design
**Status:** approved
**Module:** `backend/src/relay/config.rs`, `frontend/src/composables/useAgentConfigs.ts`, `frontend/src/views/AgentsConfigView.vue`
**Tags:** stack:both, module:api-sources
**Depends on:** ApiSources-A3, ApiSources-G3

### Overview

Replace `model_tier` in `AgentConfig` with `model_id` for direct model selection. This is a data model change, a resolution logic simplification, and a frontend UI update.

### 1. Backend Data Model Changes

**File: `backend/src/relay/config.rs`**

#### AgentConfig (current lines ~370–397)

Add `model_id: String` and keep `model_tier` as deprecated for migration:

```rust
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize)]
pub struct AgentConfig {
    pub id: String,
    pub name: String,
    pub profession_id: String,
    pub soul_id: String,
    pub api_source_id: String,
    /// Direct model reference (e.g., "claude-sonnet-4-20250514"). Replaces model_tier.
    #[serde(default)]
    pub model_id: String,
    /// Deprecated: kept for migration from legacy configs. No longer used in resolution.
    #[serde(default)]
    pub model_tier: ModelTier,
    #[serde(default)]
    pub is_default: bool,
    #[serde(default = "default_temperature")]
    pub temperature: f32,
    #[serde(default = "default_max_tokens")]
    pub max_tokens: u32,
    #[serde(default)]
    pub reasoning_budget: Option<u32>,
    #[serde(default)]
    pub thinking_enabled: bool,
    #[serde(default)]
    pub thinking_budget: Option<u32>,
    #[serde(default)]
    pub avatar_url: Option<String>,
    #[serde(default)]
    pub equipped_skills: Vec<String>,
}
```

**Key**: Both fields use `#[serde(default)]` so existing JSON files with only `model_tier` deserialize without error (model_id defaults to ""), and new files with only `model_id` also work (model_tier defaults to Min).

#### ModelDefinition (lines ~32–36) — unchanged

```rust
pub struct ModelDefinition {
    pub id: String,       // e.g., "claude-sonnet-4-20250514"
    pub name: String,     // e.g., "Claude Sonnet 4"
    pub tier: ModelTier,  // Display tag only: Min/Lite/Mid/Pro/Max
}
```

#### resolve_model() (current lines ~548–586) — simplified

Replace the entire tier downgrade walk with a direct model_id lookup:

```rust
pub fn resolve_model(
    config: &AgentConfig,
    api_sources: &[ApiSource],
) -> Option<crate::relay::agent::ModelConfig> {
    // 1. Find the ApiSource
    let source = api_sources.iter()
        .find(|s| s.id == config.api_source_id)
        .or_else(|| api_sources.first())?;

    // 2. Find the specific model by ID (direct lookup, no tier walk)
    let model_def = source.models.iter()
        .find(|m| m.id == config.model_id)
        .or_else(|| {
            log::warn!(
                "model_id '{}' not found in ApiSource '{}', falling back to first model",
                config.model_id, source.id
            );
            source.models.first()
        })?;

    Some(crate::relay::agent::ModelConfig {
        provider: source.provider.clone(),
        model: model_def.id.clone(),
        temperature: config.temperature,
        max_tokens: config.max_tokens,
        reasoning_budget: config.reasoning_budget,
        fallback_chain: Vec::new(),
    })
}
```

#### generate_default_agents_with_source() (current lines ~449–490) — updated

Generate with empty model_id; migration fills it:

```rust
pub fn generate_default_agents_with_source(api_source_id: &str) -> Vec<AgentConfig> {
    let defaults: [(&str, &str, &str, ModelTier); 9] = [
        ("assistant", "Nicole", "assistant", ModelTier::Lite),
        ("advisor", "Isaac", "advisor", ModelTier::Mid),
        ("architect", "Vera", "architect", ModelTier::Pro),
        ("planner", "Felix", "planner", ModelTier::Mid),
        ("tester", "Quinn", "tester", ModelTier::Lite),
        ("coder", "Ash", "coder", ModelTier::Mid),
        ("reviewer", "Marcus", "reviewer", ModelTier::Pro),
        ("documenter", "Luna", "documenter", ModelTier::Lite),
        ("gofer", "Gus", "gofer", ModelTier::Lite),
    ];

    defaults
        .map(|(profession, name, soul, preferred_tier)| AgentConfig {
            id: format!("default-{}", profession),
            name: name.to_string(),
            profession_id: profession.to_string(),
            soul_id: soul.to_string(),
            api_source_id: api_source_id.to_string(),
            model_id: String::new(), // filled by assign_model_ids()
            model_tier: preferred_tier,
            is_default: true,
            temperature: 0.3,
            max_tokens: if preferred_tier == ModelTier::Lite { 4096 } else { 8192 },
            reasoning_budget: if preferred_tier == ModelTier::Pro { Some(4096) } else { None },
            thinking_enabled: matches!(profession, "advisor" | "architect" | "planner" | "tester" | "coder" | "reviewer"),
            thinking_budget: match profession {
                "architect" | "coder" => Some(2048),
                "advisor" | "planner" | "tester" | "reviewer" => Some(1024),
                _ => None,
            },
            avatar_url: None,
            equipped_skills: Vec::new(),
        })
        .to_vec()
}
```

#### New: assign_model_ids() — migration helper

```rust
/// For each config with empty model_id, find the best matching model
/// from its ApiSource by preferred tier, then fallback to first model.
pub fn assign_model_ids(configs: &mut [AgentConfig], api_sources: &[ApiSource]) {
    for config in configs.iter_mut() {
        if config.model_id.is_empty() {
            let source = api_sources.iter()
                .find(|s| s.id == config.api_source_id)
                .or_else(|| api_sources.first());
            config.model_id = source
                .and_then(|s| {
                    s.models.iter().find(|m| m.tier == config.model_tier)
                        .or_else(|| s.models.first())
                })
                .map(|m| m.id.clone())
                .unwrap_or_default();

            if !config.model_id.is_empty() {
                log::info!(
                    "Migrated AgentConfig '{}': tier {:?} → model_id '{}'",
                    config.id, config.model_tier, config.model_id
                );
            }
        }
    }
}
```

#### load_or_generate_agent_configs() (current lines ~498–527) — add migration call

Insert `assign_model_ids()` call after loading/merging configs:

```rust
pub fn load_or_generate_agent_configs(api_sources: &[ApiSource]) -> Vec<AgentConfig> {
    let existing = load_agent_configs();
    let defaults = generate_default_agents_with_source(
        api_sources.first().map(|s| s.id.as_str()).unwrap_or(""),
    );

    let mut merged = if existing.is_empty() {
        defaults
    } else {
        let first_source_id = api_sources.first().map(|s| s.id.as_str()).unwrap_or("");
        let mut merged: Vec<AgentConfig> = existing.into_iter().map(|mut c| {
            if c.api_source_id.is_empty() && !first_source_id.is_empty() {
                c.api_source_id = first_source_id.to_string();
            }
            c
        }).collect();

        for default in &defaults {
            if !merged.iter().any(|c| c.id == default.id) {
                merged.push(default.clone());
            }
        }
        merged
    };

    // MIGRATION: Fill model_id for configs that only have model_tier
    assign_model_ids(&mut merged, api_sources);

    let _ = save_agent_configs(&merged);
    merged
}
```

