### 4. Error Handling

| Error Case | Handling |
|------------|----------|
| `model_id` not found in ApiSource | Fallback to first model, log warning via `log::warn!` |
| `api_source_id` not found | Fallback to first ApiSource + first model |
| ApiSource has no models | Return `None` from `resolve_model()`, agent spawn fails gracefully |
| Legacy config with `model_tier` but no `model_id` | Auto-migrate on load via `assign_model_ids()`: tier → first matching model |
| ApiSource deleted while agents reference it | `resolve_model()` falls back to first ApiSource; UI shows source not found |

### 5. Files Modified

| File | Change |
|------|--------|
| `backend/src/relay/config.rs` | Add `model_id: String` to AgentConfig; simplify `resolve_model()` to direct lookup; add `assign_model_ids()` for migration; update `generate_default_agents_with_source()` |
| `backend/src/relay/mod.rs` | No logic change — `RelayRegistry` already uses `resolve_model()` for all model resolution |
| `frontend/src/composables/useAgentConfigs.ts` | Add `model_id` to `AgentConfigDto`; keep `model_tier` for display |
| `frontend/src/composables/useApiSources.ts` | Add `getModelsForSource(sourceId)` helper |
| `frontend/src/views/AgentsConfigView.vue` | Replace tier dropdown with model selector listing models from selected ApiSource with tier badges |
| `frontend/src/locales/en.json` | Add `agents.model` key |
| `frontend/src/locales/zh.json` | Add `agents.model` key |

### 6. Data Lifecycle

```
[Default Generation]
  api_sources loaded → generate_default_agents_with_source() → model_id left empty
  → assign_model_ids() fills model_id from preferred tier match
  → saved to agent_configs.json

[User Edit]
  User opens AgentConfig → UI shows model list for selected ApiSource
  → User picks model → model_id saved; model_tier updated from selected model's tier

[Agent Spawn]
  Orchestrator → resolve_model(config, api_sources)
  → find ModelDefinition by model_id (direct lookup, no tier walk)
  → return ModelConfig(provider, model_id, params)
  → AgentInstance spawned with resolved model

[ApiSource Model Change]
  If referenced model_id removed from ApiSource
  → resolve_model falls back to first model + log warning
  → UI shows "Model not found" indicator on AgentConfig card

[Legacy Config Migration]
  Load agent_configs.json → model_id is empty, model_tier present
  → assign_model_ids() converts tier → first matching model in ApiSource
  → Saved back with model_id populated
```

