| `model_id` not found in ApiSource | Fallback to first model, log warning |
| `api_source_id` not found | Fallback to first ApiSource + first model |
| ApiSource has no models | Return `None` from `resolve_model()`, agent spawn fails gracefully |
| Legacy config with `model_tier` but no `model_id` | Auto-migrate on load: tier → first matching model |
| ApiSource deleted while agents reference it | Agent shows "API Source not found" warning in UI, cannot spawn |

### 5. Files Modified

| File | Change |
|------|--------|
| `backend/src/relay/config.rs` | AgentConfig: `model_tier` → `model_id`; simplify `resolve_model()`; update defaults; add migration |
| `backend/src/relay/mod.rs` | `spawn_agent_from_config()` — no logic change (already uses `resolve_model()`) |
| `frontend/src/composables/useAgentConfigs.ts` | `model_tier` → `model_id` in `AgentConfigDto` |
| `frontend/src/composables/useApiSources.ts` | Add helper: `getModelsForSource(sourceId)` |
| `frontend/src/views/AgentsConfigView.vue` | Replace tier dropdown with model selector |
| `frontend/src/locales/en.json` | Update model selection keys |
| `frontend/src/locales/zh.json` | Update model selection keys |

### 6. Data Lifecycle

```
[Default Generation]
  api_sources loaded → generate_default_configs() → picks concrete model_id per tier preference
  → saved to agent_configs.json

[User Edit]
  User opens AgentConfig → UI shows model list for selected ApiSource
  → User picks model → model_id saved

[Agent Spawn]
  Orchestrator → resolve_model(config, api_sources)
  → find ModelDefinition by model_id
  → return ModelConfig(provider, model_id, params)
  → AgentInstance spawned with resolved model

[ApiSource Model Change]
  If referenced model_id removed from ApiSource
  → resolve_model falls back to first model + log warning
  → UI shows "Model not found" indicator on AgentConfig
```

